o points out that certain principles of Athenian maritime law are still imbedded in the modern international law of maritime commerce.Originally published in 1973.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCourtsxGreecexAthensxHistory. 0aCourtszGreecexAthensxHistory. 0aCourtszGreecezAthensxHistory. 0aCourts. 0aDroit maritimezGrècexAthènesxHistoire. 0aMaritime lawxGreecexAthensxHistory. 0aMaritime lawzGreecexAthensxHistory. 0aMaritime lawzGreecezAthensxHistory. 0aMaritime law. 0aTribunauxxGrècexAthènesxHistoire. 7aLAW / Military.2bisacsh1 aCohen, Edward, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979z978311042684708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Law & Political Sciencez978311041351908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140086781340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400867813423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400867813.jpg  a978-3-11-041351-9  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Law & Political Science  a978-3-11-042684-7  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979c193